-- South Africa Richards Bay Coal Prices Advance to Two-Month High
-- B y   R o b   V e r d o n c k
-- 2012-11-26T16:51:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-26/south-africa-richards-bay-coal-prices-advance-to-two-month-high.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, rose for a third week to their highest level in more than
two months.  Coal for  immediate delivery  added $1.14, or 1.3 percent, to
$87.57 a metric ton in the week to Nov. 23, according to IHS
McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the highest level since
Sept. 7. The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Verdonck in London at 
 rverdonck@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
